15:55.890 --> 15:58.957
He's, uh, nobody.

15:58.959 --> 16:00.225
He looks rich.

16:03.230 --> 16:04.096
All right.

16:04.098 --> 16:06.098
There's no cameras
in the place.

16:06.100 --> 16:07.566
No cameras in
the parking lot.

16:07.568 --> 16:08.833
It's just a bunch
of teenage girls

16:08.835 --> 16:12.036
scooping ice cream
for minimum wage.

16:12.038 --> 16:13.371
Did you take
the picture?

16:13.373 --> 16:14.973
Yep.
And she'll be there?

16:14.975 --> 16:16.174
Where else
is she gonna be?

16:16.176 --> 16:17.242
It's the middle
of nowhere.

16:17.244 --> 16:18.843
She's never
missed a shift.

16:18.845 --> 16:19.812
Good.

16:22.649 --> 16:23.515
Who is she?

16:25.986 --> 16:29.321
Come on, J. You have me
stalking a teenage girl.

16:29.323 --> 16:31.656
I'm not gonna ask her
to blow you.

16:31.658 --> 16:33.325
You're not that funny,
you know that?

16:36.463 --> 16:39.131
When are you
gonna be home?

16:39.133 --> 16:40.132
Soon.

16:40.134 --> 16:41.466
I'm not
your hooker.

16:41.468 --> 16:45.337
Well, I pay you,
and we have sex,

16:45.339 --> 16:47.205
so what does
that make you?

16:47.207 --> 16:49.474
If I was charging you
for the sex,

16:49.476 --> 16:52.144
you'd be paying
a lot more.

16:52.146 --> 16:53.345
Do you miss me?

16:53.347 --> 16:54.813
No.

16:54.815 --> 16:57.015
I just want to make sure I'm not
boning two dudes on the couch

16:57.017 --> 16:58.083
when you walk in.

17:00.754 --> 17:04.489
You can't just come and go
whenever you want.

17:04.491 --> 17:06.558
I can.

17:06.560 --> 17:07.792
It's my house.

17:25.244 --> 17:26.845
Craig: You can't let Adrian
quit the tour, man.

17:26.847 --> 17:28.180
Deran: Jesus,
you're still on this?

17:28.182 --> 17:30.515
Yo, he will never
forgive you.

17:30.517 --> 17:31.916
It's his choice.

17:31.918 --> 17:33.185
You heard
what he said.

17:33.187 --> 17:35.053
"It's a lot of time away."
He doesn't trust you.

17:35.055 --> 17:36.188
Bullshit.

17:36.190 --> 17:37.856
Gay dudes get around, man.

17:37.858 --> 17:39.457
Oh, yeah?
Tell me more about gay dudes.

17:39.459 --> 17:40.459
No, look,
I'm just saying...

17:40.461 --> 17:41.593
There's only one person
in this car

17:41.595 --> 17:43.928
who's had antibiotic-resistant
gonorrhea twice,

17:43.930 --> 17:46.331
and it's not me.

17:46.333 --> 17:49.802
We live together, okay?
He trusts me.

17:49.804 --> 17:52.137
You, um,
talk to Pope lately?

17:54.208 --> 17:56.608
Yeah.

17:56.610 --> 17:59.344
When?

17:59.346 --> 18:00.979
I don't know.
I talk to him. Why?

18:03.017 --> 18:05.750
He seem a little off
to you?

18:05.752 --> 18:07.552
Are you kidding me?

18:07.554 --> 18:10.955
Well, like, since Lena's left,
he's, uh...

18:10.957 --> 18:12.024
weird, right?

18:12.026 --> 18:13.091
Yeah, yeah.
He's a weird guy.

18:13.093 --> 18:15.293
No, but, like,
extra weird.

18:15.295 --> 18:17.095
How about this one?

18:17.097 --> 18:18.563
Sure.

18:18.565 --> 18:21.700
I mean, he doesn't
leave the house,

18:21.702 --> 18:23.836
hardly eats,
never sleeps.

18:23.838 --> 18:26.638
And now, Smurf's got him doing
this MMA shit again.

18:26.640 --> 18:29.441
Well, Pope's always gotten off
on that kind of shit.

18:29.443 --> 18:31.844
He's got that look...

18:31.846 --> 18:33.846
like he doesn't care
what happens to him.

18:35.850 --> 18:37.483
Like he could
hurt somebody.

18:41.588 --> 18:43.722
What are you saying?

18:43.724 --> 18:47.926
You think it's okay
he's on this thing?

18:47.928 --> 18:49.061
Hmm?

18:49.063 --> 18:51.463
You want to go and tell Pope
he's off the job,

18:51.465 --> 18:53.331
go for it.

18:53.333 --> 18:56.669
Yo, someone
looks at him sideways,

18:56.671 --> 18:58.737
we're gonna be accessories
to murder, man.

19:00.807 --> 19:03.876
He's not gonna
kill anybody.

19:03.878 --> 19:06.611
Besides, this is Smurf's job,
and she says he's on the job,

19:06.613 --> 19:09.214
so he's on the job, okay?

19:09.216 --> 19:10.115
Let's do this.

19:13.888 --> 19:15.019
[ Slams car door ]

19:15.021 --> 19:17.890
♪♪

19:20.026 --> 19:22.995
♪♪

19:25.165 --> 19:27.900
Everything set
for tomorrow?

19:27.902 --> 19:30.369
Yeah.

19:30.371 --> 19:32.905
The girl?

19:32.907 --> 19:33.972
Yeah.

19:33.974 --> 19:34.907
Good.

19:39.580 --> 19:40.979
Is the money
gonna be there?

19:40.981 --> 19:43.916
16 farms
use that place, baby.

19:43.918 --> 19:45.517
They pay in cash,

19:45.519 --> 19:50.322
and the money is there for
24 hours before every payday.

19:50.324 --> 19:52.857
You sure we can get past
the cameras?

19:52.859 --> 19:55.594
I don't think anybody's
gonna be talking to the cops

19:55.596 --> 19:59.131
about money used
to pay illegal workers.

19:59.133 --> 20:01.533
Where did you sleep
last night?

20:01.535 --> 20:02.867
My girlfriend's place.

20:02.869 --> 20:04.269
Oh, that's right.

20:04.271 --> 20:08.073
The one that I am still
not allowed to meet.

20:08.075 --> 20:10.609
No, no. She... She just
works weird hours.

20:10.611 --> 20:12.144
I'll bring her by soon.

20:12.146 --> 20:14.580
You know, J,
I'm just curious...

20:16.150 --> 20:21.486
are you hiding her from us,
or is it the other way around?

20:21.488 --> 20:23.822
I'm not hiding her.

20:23.824 --> 20:26.358
Why aren't you wearing
the watch I bought you?

20:26.360 --> 20:28.426
[ Gate opens ]

20:28.428 --> 20:30.763
It's too nice.
I don't want to lose it.

20:30.765 --> 20:34.566
Oh, I understand.

20:34.568 --> 20:37.902
Gentlemen. Adrian.
Everybody hungry?

20:37.904 --> 20:39.371
Adrian: Starving.

20:39.373 --> 20:41.840
Craig: The dude in 4B
shoots up in the bathtub,

20:41.842 --> 20:44.843
falls asleep,
floods the apartment.

20:44.845 --> 20:46.845
The lady in 3B,
Mrs. Andrews,

20:46.847 --> 20:49.314
with the, um...
- Egg thing on her neck?

20:49.316 --> 20:50.315
That's a goiter.

20:50.317 --> 20:51.383
- Mm-hmm.
- Yeah.

20:51.385 --> 20:52.717
Deran: Whatever it is,
it's nasty.

20:52.719 --> 20:55.788
Dude's bathtub is directly above
her cat's room.

20:55.790 --> 20:56.855
Uh-huh.

20:56.857 --> 20:58.323
Wait, her cat has
its own bedroom?

20:58.325 --> 20:59.257
- Oh, yeah.
- Yeah.

20:59.259 --> 21:01.059
That old bitch
loves her cats.

21:01.061 --> 21:03.462
So, then, she walks up the
stairs with a shotgun,

21:03.464 --> 21:05.730
and threatens to shoot him
in the face.

21:05.732 --> 21:08.132
I spent the whole weekend
at Whaley,

21:08.134 --> 21:09.401
trying to talk
my tenants down

21:09.403 --> 21:11.136
from having
an all-out bloodbath.

21:15.609 --> 21:16.542
Deran: Pope.

21:19.546 --> 21:21.279
Slow down.

21:21.281 --> 21:22.881
When's the party?

21:22.883 --> 21:24.683
We're not
having a party.

21:24.685 --> 21:26.951
Of course you are.
Adrian?

21:26.953 --> 21:29.688
- What's that?
- When's the party?

21:29.690 --> 21:31.223
Like, a housewarming?

21:31.225 --> 21:34.359
Smurf: It's like a maiden voyage
for your house.

21:34.361 --> 21:36.094
Because it will not
be a home

21:36.096 --> 21:39.097
until you trash it
with the ones you love.

21:39.099 --> 21:40.432
Deran: Yeah, well,
we just bought the house,

21:40.434 --> 21:42.767
so I don't know if we want to
go and trash it already.

21:42.769 --> 21:45.170
When I bought this house...
Pope remembers...

21:45.172 --> 21:47.639
we partied for
about four days.

21:47.641 --> 21:51.309
People were sleeping everywhere,
cooking, playing music.

21:51.311 --> 21:52.845
Fetu.
Remember Fetu?

21:52.847 --> 21:54.112
Craig?
- Wait, who?

21:54.114 --> 21:56.981
The Samoan guy who owned
the crab shack on Pacific.

21:56.983 --> 21:57.982
The guy that used to be
the Santa

21:57.984 --> 21:59.584
at the, uh,
Christmas parade, right?

21:59.586 --> 22:00.985
- That's right.
- Yeah. I remember that guy.

22:00.987 --> 22:02.721
He's the reason I was afraid
of Santa when I was little.

22:02.723 --> 22:04.189
[ Laughter ]

22:07.461 --> 22:08.560
Where are you going?

22:11.131 --> 22:12.131
I'm done.

22:25.412 --> 22:26.945
What's wrong with him?

22:26.947 --> 22:28.146
Nothing. He's fine.

22:28.148 --> 22:29.682
He's his normal self.

22:32.686 --> 22:34.086
Is he taking his meds?

22:35.890 --> 22:40.492
Adrian, would you like to get
the dessert plates, please?

22:40.494 --> 22:41.794
Yeah. Sure.

22:47.033 --> 22:49.368
Deran: Pope looks like
a human punching bag.

22:49.370 --> 22:50.969
And I don't think he should
go on the job.

22:50.971 --> 22:51.904
Craig agrees with me.

22:51.906 --> 22:53.171
What the hell, man?

22:53.173 --> 22:54.773
The job is risky enough
without Pope, okay?

22:54.775 --> 22:56.909
He's out of his mind right now.
He's gonna get us all killed.

22:56.911 --> 22:58.042
J, tell her.

22:58.044 --> 23:01.045
[ J speaks indistinctly ]
Zip it!

23:01.047 --> 23:03.716
- Smurf...
- He's in.

23:03.718 --> 23:05.250
Now, who wants dessert?

23:07.454 --> 23:09.421
[ Footsteps walking inside ]

23:13.860 --> 23:16.729
